The paper proposes a method for instance segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves learning a pixel-pair affinity pyramid and a cascaded graph partition module, which are both based on machine learning techniques (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results on a challenging dataset, which suggests a focus on performance evaluation (cs.CL). Finally, the method involves grouping pixels into different object instances, which could be related to robotics (cs.RO).
